KINGDOM DAY PARADE ROUTE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The <DATE>1990</DATE> <ORGANIZATION>Kingdom Day Parade</ORGANIZATION> will be held <DATE>Monday</DATE> to commemorate the <DATE>Jan. 15 
birthday</DATE> of slain civil rights leader <ORGANIZATION>Martin Luther King Jr</ORGANIZATION>. 
</P>
<P>
<ORGANIZATION>Martin Luther King Jr</ORGANIZATION>. Boulevard will be closed to traffic and parking. 
</P>
<P>
Parade will begin at <TIME>11 a.m.</TIME> 
</P>
<P>
Starting point is at <PERSON>Crenshaw</PERSON> and <ORGANIZATION>Martin Luther King Jr.</ORGANIZATION> boulevards. 
</P>
<P>
Reviewing stand for judges will be at <ORGANIZATION>Martin Luther King Jr</ORGANIZATION>. Blvd. near <ORGANIZATION>McClung 
Drive</ORGANIZATION>. 
</P>
<P>
Termination point will be at the <ORGANIZATION>Los Angeles Coliseum</ORGANIZATION> at <LOCATION>Menlo</LOCATION> and 39th 
streets. 
</P>
<P>
Registration and parade assignments will be at <ORGANIZATION>Martin Luther King Jr</ORGANIZATION>. Boulevard 
and <LOCATION>Marlton Avenue</LOCATION>. 
</P>
<P>
Grand marshal will be <PERSON>Ruth Washington</PERSON>, publisher of the <LOCATION>Los Angeles Sentinel</LOCATION>. 
</P>
<P>
More than 4,000 people are expected to participate. 
</P></TEXT>
